E. o. aman. v. patolog, inst. i Upps. 33’-34, assist :läk. samt e. läk. v. Garn:sjukh. i Boden fcir. avd. 3i6-3i7, und :l>äk. v. Roimanäs sanat. 38, üäk. v. Tranérska stift, i Torpa 39-45, prakt. translated: Kallstenius, Bengt, prakt, läkare, Tranås, b. 14/5/05 in Upps. to professor, Ph.D. Gottfrid K. and Hildegard Maria Elisabet Örtienhoilm. Married in 1932 to Siri Hildegard Landstätt. Children: Per Gottfrid b. 1933, Lars Richard b. 1939, Lena Hildegard b. 1942. — Obtained high school diploma in Västerås in 1925, medical candidate degree in Uppsala in 1929, and medical licentiate degree there in 1936. Temporary assistant at the pathological institute in Uppsala from 1933-1934, assistant doctor and physician at Garn:sjukh in Boden in surgical department from 1936-1937, resident physician at Roimanäs sanatorium in 1938, district physician at Tranérska stift, in Torpa from 1939-1945, practicing physician in Tranås since 1940.
